edar\n|\nCrying is good for the soul. It means something needs to be released. And if you don't release the something, it just weighs you down until you can hardly move.\n\n- Erin Entrada Kelly, Hello, Universe\n|\nWhen a Lady chooses to Change Her Mind,' said the Mouse with a touch of hauteur, 'a Gentleman would consider it no more than her Privilege, and not Badger Her About It.\n\n- Noel Langley, The Land of Green Ginger\n|\nLove, kindness, compassion and forgiveness are divine.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nA lovely girl gazing at the stars, and the stars who gazed back.\n\n- Sarah J. Maas, Throne of Glass\n|\nThe expensive car you bought doesn’t matter, but the way you treated the sales man did.\n\n- Sheila\n|\nHere, in this quiet place we own, worlds are born.\n\n- Cassandra\n|\nI am fighting to stay alive not because I fear death, but because I love life.\n\n- Edie Littlefield Sundby, The Mission Walker: I was given three months to live...\n|\nEven though friends say they are interested in your life, they never really want to talk about you as much as you want them to. (68)\n\n- Charise Mericle Harper, Flashcards of My Life\n|\nHe's never known anything like it! But then, he has never known anything to write home about, so this is nothing to write home about.\n\n- Tom Stoppard, Rosencrantz and Guildenstern Are Dead\n|\nIt hurts to breathe. It hurts to live. I hate her, yet I do not think I can exist without her.\n\n- Charlotte Featherstone, Addicted\n|\nAs a species, wise, harmonious progress is our mission.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, I Am The Thread: My Mission\n|\nLife works in mysterious ways, and I believe one of the biggest challenges and successes is to let go and let it be.\n\n- Brittany Burgunder, Safety in Numbers: From 56 to 221 Pounds, My Battle with Eating Disorders\n|\nI had a renewal of mind, when I begin to read.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nUm, enough apologies, okay?Just get on with being your badass self.\n\n- Scott\n|\nNever stop dreaming, wake up and chase your dreams.\